swift/obj/server.py.message:
for new/updated objects we could have the s3api middleware add 'generic' sysmeta such as: 

  X-Object-Sysmeta-Expirer-Params = 'type=mpu; upload_id=xyz; num_segments=123'

and have the object server stick this into the content-type without needing to understand the meaning.

  if 'X-Object-Sysmeta-Expirer-Params' in orig_metadata:
      content-type = 'application/expiry;%s' % orig_metadata['X-Object-Sysmeta-Expirer-Params']
  else:
      content-type = text/plain

or even more direct:

  X-Object-Sysmeta-Expirer-Content-Type = 'application/expiry; type=mpu; upload_id=xyz; num_segments=123'

specs/victoria/helm-config.rst.message:
This is a very common missconseption, I'm trying to make clear. The fact that the client takes a values file, doesn't mean it sends a file. The content is becoming a dict and sent to the server.

This:
 helm_values:
   prometheus-operator:
     nameOverride: prometheus
     fullnameOverride: prometheus
     alertmanager:
       alertmanagerSpec:
         image:
           repository: quay.io/prometheus/alertmanager
         priorityClassName: "system-cluster-critical"
     # Dashboard
     grafana:
       resources:
         requests:
           cpu: 100m
           memory: 128Mi
       script: |
         #!/bin.bash
         #
         echo "Hello ${name}"
     kubeApiServer:
       tlsConfig:
         insecureSkipVerify: true

becomes:
  "helm_values": {
    "prometheus-operator": {
      "nameOverride": "prometheus",
      "fullnameOverride": "prometheus",
      "alertmanager": {
        "alertmanagerSpec": {
          "image": {
            "repository": "quay.io/prometheus/alertmanager"
          },
          "priorityClassName": "system-cluster-critical"
        }
      },
      "grafana": {
        "resources": {
          "requests": {
            "cpu": "100m",
            "memory": "128Mi"
          }
        },
        "script": "#!/bin.bash\n#\necho \"Hello ${name}\"\n"
      },
      "kubeApiServer": {
        "tlsConfig": {
          "insecureSkipVerify": true
        }
      }
    }
  }

